Event Messages For websocket connections, spontaneous events will be periodically sent to clients which announce changes which happen within the middleware itself. These events will always have the following form:
{ &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;event&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;api_class_or_subsystem&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : {} } Where the contents of the arguments object is determined by the type of event (the &ldquo;name&rdquo; field). See the documentation on the individual API calls for details on the events that each call may generate or be impacted by.
 Example event message from the creation of a new user account:  { &quot;namespace&quot; : &quot;event&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : &quot;users/add&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;&quot;, &quot;args&quot; : {} }
